<DOC><DOCNO> AP890622-0112 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-22-89 1220EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Pope-Ecology     06-22 0158</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Pope-Ecology,0162</SECOND><HEAD>Pope Dedicates Peace Day to Ecology</HEAD><DATELINE>VATICAN CITY (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Pope John Paul II has dedicated the church'snext World Day of Peace to the ecological crisis, the Vatican saidThursday.   Stressing that the goods of the Earth must not be used ``forselfish ends, for profit or power alone,'' the Vatican said the needto respect the environment is a new challenge to peace.   ``Peace with God the Creator _ Peace with all of Creation'' isthe theme for the day, which the Roman Catholic Church marks on Jan.1.   The theme chosen by the pope, it said, is an invitation toreflect on the ecological crisis from a moral perspective.   ``The Earth and all that it contains are a common heritage forhumanity. This should be the governing principle for the use of thegoods of the Earth by nations and the international community towhich these goods are entrusted,'' the Vatican said.</TEXT></DOC>